In order to get at the rainfall process itself, let‚Äôs look at the distribution of rainfall events. We can find all the days of rainfall by simply filtering our DataFrame to find days when rain was greater than zero. To do this, we can use the loc() function.
The following line of code returns a new dataframe that contains only the rows where 'Rainfall (mm)' is greater than zero:
